ZH: 他对我们的困境完全无动于衷。
EN: He is completely indifferent to our predicament.

ZH: 她听到这个消息后，居然无动于衷。
EN: She was surprisingly indifferent after hearing the news.

ZH: 他对这种虐待动物的行为毫不感兴趣，完全无动于衷。
EN: He is completely indifferent to this kind of animal abuse, showing no interest whatsoever.

ZH: 我们的请求一再被无动于衷地忽视了。
EN: Our requests have been repeatedly ignored with indifference.

ZH: 这个问题即使引起争议，他还是无动于衷。
EN: He remains indifferent even if the issue causes controversy.

ZH: 他的反应让我觉得他完全无动于衷。
EN: His reaction made me feel that he is completely indifferent.

ZH: 无论别人对他说什么，他总是无动于衷。
EN: No matter what others say to him, he always remains indifferent.

ZH: 对于困境，我并不无动于衷。
EN: I am not indifferent to difficulties.

ZH: 在他的脸上，我看不出任何无动于衷的情绪。
EN: I can't detect any indifference on his face.

ZH: 他对努力学习完全无动于衷。
EN: He is completely indifferent to studying hard.

ZH: 利益和名誉对他来说都是无动于衷的东西。
EN: Both profit and fame are indifferent to him.

ZH: 他的言行总是让人感到无动于衷的态度。
EN: His words and actions always give a sense of indifference.

ZH: 尽管发生了那么严重的事故，他还是保持了无动于衷的态度。
EN: Despite the serious accident, he remained indifferent.

ZH: 无论别人怎么说，她都始终无动于衷。
EN: No matter what others say, she remains indifferent.

ZH: 在浩大的人潮中，他显得无动于衷。
EN: Among the massive crowd, he seemed indifferent.

ZH: 老师再三叮嘱，但他依然无动于衷。
EN: Despite the teacher's repeated admonition, he remained indifferent.

ZH: 这个败家子对于金钱无动于衷。
EN: This prodigal son is indifferent to money.

ZH: 他对别人的困难总是能保持无动于衷。
EN: He always manages to remain indifferent to other people's difficulties.

ZH: 尽管工作出了问题，他仍然无动于衷。
EN: Despite the work problems, he still remained indifferent.

ZH: 无论发生什么事情，他都保持着无动于衷的面容。
EN: Whatever happens, he maintains an indifferent expression.
